The paper discusses the use of SKOS for expressing controlled vocabularies, which is a common topic in natural language processing and information retrieval (cs.IR), as well as in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for knowledge representation. The paper also discusses potential quality issues in using SKOS, which is related to database management (cs.DB) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper provides validation rules for assessing the quality of SKOS mappings, which could be relevant to deep learning (cs.DL) for developing automated systems to improve the quality of mappings.
